    "Dunbar Track Team Defeat Franklin The Dunbar Wolverines last gears city track champs ran to their fourth consecutive dual track triumph in easy fashion yester day afternoon when they de feated Franklin 90 to 28 Double victors for the Wolverines were Sam Mukes who won the 100 and 220 yard dashes and Tom Henderson who won the 120 yard low and high hurdles Ernie Phil pot won the pole vault and discus throw for Franklin Caldwell of Dunbar made a shot put heave of 45 feet 7 inches to clinch the outstanding perform ance of the day The results 100 yard dash Mukes D Bot tles F Cranes D time 0105 220 yard dash Mukes D_ Fritz D_ Cranes D time 024 440 yard dash Cofield D Taner D Reid D time 0555 880 yard dash Owens D Kil gore D Culbreath D time 2141 Gus Lesnevich In Exhibition With Shelton Bell Promter A1 Menachof an nounced yesterday that he had signed Oakland Billy Smith a top ranking light heavyweight to a 10round match with Charley Banks of Cincinnati Monday April 26 It will be one of two 10round ers scheduled for the card The other 10rounder will offer Jesse"
